35:46.778 --> 35:49.215
The Griddle House started
as a soup kitchen.

35:49.215 --> 35:52.117
For years that house gave
away every bit of food

35:52.117 --> 35:57.122
it could chef up so
there is no imposing,

35:57.122 --> 36:00.259
there is no troubling anybody

36:01.860 --> 36:05.364
'cause this building
was made to give

36:05.364 --> 36:07.266
everything it's
got and then some.

36:11.036 --> 36:11.870
Tiny,

36:13.905 --> 36:14.940
I was just like you.

36:14.940 --> 36:17.609
- No.
- Yes I was.

36:20.579 --> 36:23.982
I am living proof of
a life turned around.

36:26.418 --> 36:29.120
I've never told anybody that.

36:34.092 --> 36:35.327
Let's make that call huh?

36:38.897 --> 36:42.067
- My voice is gonna shake.
- End it.

36:55.581 --> 36:56.915
- Johnny.

36:58.617 --> 37:02.288
My car broke, I'm
trying to get it fixed.

37:04.256 --> 37:06.958
I'll get there as soon as I can.

37:11.196 --> 37:12.631
He hung up on me.

37:16.635 --> 37:18.970
I'm sorry.

37:22.674 --> 37:23.675
- It's okay.

37:24.810 --> 37:27.779
It's okay, it's okay.

37:27.779 --> 37:29.748
- Excuse me can I help you?

37:29.748 --> 37:30.982
What are you doing back here?

37:30.982 --> 37:32.117
Are you trying to
steal my recipe

37:32.117 --> 37:34.420
for the best sandwich
in the world?

37:36.355 --> 37:40.191
- Yeah, I'm just
a little lost I guess.

37:40.191 --> 37:41.159
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

37:43.662 --> 37:46.131
Mae-Bee's a strange
name isn't it?

37:46.131 --> 37:47.833
Maybe yes, like maybe no.

37:49.034 --> 37:50.536
- Not really, it's
not her real name,

37:50.536 --> 37:53.071
her real name is Maybelline
like the Chuck Berry song.

37:53.071 --> 37:55.474
It's not an abbreviation
for indecisiveness.

37:56.642 --> 38:01.380
- Oh and Tiny, I mean,
that's a weird one.

38:03.248 --> 38:05.751
- You know I don't even
know what her real name is.

38:05.751 --> 38:06.985
Tiny is all we ever called her.

38:06.985 --> 38:08.687
I gotta ask her
one of these days.

38:09.988 --> 38:13.892
- So how long you been
working here and stuff?

38:13.892 --> 38:15.126
- I was just driving
down the highway,

38:15.126 --> 38:17.228
I stopped here for
a cup of coffee.

38:17.228 --> 38:21.032
It's been 30 years,
I better call home.

38:21.032 --> 38:22.534
- So do you like it?

38:22.534 --> 38:24.035
I mean do you like the people?

38:25.471 --> 38:28.239
- Are you asking me if I
got a crush on somebody?

38:28.239 --> 38:29.508
- No.

38:29.508 --> 38:31.042
- Maybe you have a
crush on somebody?

38:32.611 --> 38:34.279
- No.
- It's okay now.

38:34.279 --> 38:35.814
They're attractive, but a
little old for you but--

38:35.814 --> 38:38.584
- No, no I was just,

38:40.486 --> 38:42.654
I was just wondering
if, you know,

38:42.654 --> 38:45.090
you liked working with
Francis and Mae-Bee.

38:45.090 --> 38:47.893
- Yeah, yeah, I like
working with them.

38:49.294 --> 38:50.195
- What about Tiny?

38:52.898 --> 38:53.999
- Well you know Tiny,

38:56.234 --> 38:57.569
Tiny's different you know.

38:58.970 --> 39:00.539
- Different how?

39:00.539 --> 39:03.041
- She just doesn't know
she's home yet you know.

39:03.041 --> 39:03.875
- Home.

39:06.044 --> 39:06.978
Right.

39:06.978 --> 39:09.848
So you all live around here?

39:11.450 --> 39:12.283
- Yeah.

39:13.452 --> 39:15.153
Paxton might not
be all that much,

39:15.153 --> 39:17.255
but it holds all our hearts.

39:18.256 --> 39:20.191
You know who wrote that?
- Who?

39:20.191 --> 39:21.126
- Francis.

39:50.321 --> 39:51.623
- Excuse me ma'am.

39:51.623 --> 39:54.760
♪ It was a Monday that
felt like a Tuesday ♪

39:54.760 --> 39:56.795
♪ And after noon
turned into night ♪

39:56.795 --> 40:01.099
Yeah I was wondering if I
could ask you some questions?

40:01.099 --> 40:02.233
- Okay.

40:02.233 --> 40:04.402
- Like sit down questions.

40:04.402 --> 40:07.038
You're a writer, this
is like an interview.

40:07.939 --> 40:10.308
- Like for school or something?

40:10.308 --> 40:12.243
- Yeah, yeah for my school.

40:13.645 --> 40:17.315
- Okay, let me just
set these down.

40:20.552 --> 40:24.990
Okay, well, nobody's ever wanted
to interview me before, so.

40:25.924 --> 40:27.258
- Francis right?
- Yeah.

40:28.694 --> 40:32.498
Francis Beemer, Francis
Rose Beemer, B-E-E-M-E-R.

40:32.498 --> 40:34.700
It's kind of like a fancy
name don't you think?

40:34.700 --> 40:36.535
Kind of famous fancy.

40:37.703 --> 40:39.004
I always thought maybe like

40:39.004 --> 40:41.473
it would be like
Earhart and Beemer.

40:41.473 --> 40:42.874
I could be her
copilot or something,

40:42.874 --> 40:44.476
that's the kind of name it is.

40:44.476 --> 40:45.744
Oh and you know what

40:45.744 --> 40:47.378
I always wanted to
see my name in print

40:47.378 --> 40:48.947
so it's my first time.

40:50.582 --> 40:51.382
- Okay.

40:52.450 --> 40:54.119
Which state were you born in?

40:54.119 --> 40:58.624
- Oh honey I was born right
here in 1959 Mother's Day

40:58.624 --> 41:00.692
and I have only left
the state three times.

41:01.827 --> 41:04.429
- That makes you 35?

41:04.429 --> 41:07.766
That makes me 36, I'm
a little bit older.

41:10.502 --> 41:13.805
- Okay what is your hair color?

41:13.805 --> 41:17.876
- Well this is actually a rinse,

41:17.876 --> 41:22.881
but my hair color it's actually
more like the color brown

41:23.615 --> 41:24.783
like yours, that color.

41:24.783 --> 41:26.051
- So your hair color's
naturally brown?

41:26.051 --> 41:28.119
- Well I was born as
bald as a cue ball,

41:28.119 --> 41:29.521
but once my hair
started coming in,

41:29.521 --> 41:31.456
yeah pine cone
brown is what I got.

41:31.456 --> 41:32.290
- Okay.

41:34.660 --> 41:36.595
Do you like to play outside?

41:36.595 --> 41:38.396
- Come again?

41:38.396 --> 41:40.398
- Do you like to play
outside like on a swing set

41:40.398 --> 41:42.033
or seesaw or something?

41:42.033 --> 41:44.402
- Sure, yeah,
outside's friendly.

41:45.737 --> 41:47.539
Can I ask you what
is this for again?

41:48.940 --> 41:50.208
- Are you left handed?

41:50.208 --> 41:53.745
- Oh, well actually
I'm ambidextrous.

41:53.745 --> 41:56.014
- What does that mean?

41:56.014 --> 41:57.348
- Ambidextrous.

41:57.348 --> 41:58.884
It means that I do
things with both hands.

41:58.884 --> 42:01.787
I can write with both hands,
I can cut with both hands.

42:01.787 --> 42:03.822
- Wow that is amazing.

42:06.825 --> 42:07.926
Ambidextrous.

42:09.661 --> 42:11.563
Do you like movies?
- I love movies.

42:11.563 --> 42:14.265
I mean when I was a little kid
we used to go to the movies.

42:14.265 --> 42:17.903
I just, I love it, I love it.

42:17.903 --> 42:19.370
- Me too.

42:19.370 --> 42:23.575
Do you get like one big
bad cold during the winter?

42:23.575 --> 42:27.445
- Oh, yeah when I get a
cold yeah it's big and bad.

42:27.445 --> 42:28.580
- Well okay.

42:34.452 --> 42:35.721
Do you like children?

42:35.721 --> 42:36.822
- Do I like children?

42:37.723 --> 42:39.591
Yeah I like children.

42:41.492 --> 42:42.460
What's not to like?

42:43.929 --> 42:47.999
- What about the name Jack?
- Yeah I like the name Jack.

42:47.999 --> 42:50.468
I also like the name Phil.

42:50.468 --> 42:52.570
Okay I'm sorry Phil,
but I've gotta go.

42:52.570 --> 42:54.539
- Just one more
question, one more.

42:54.539 --> 42:55.874
One more question or two more.

42:55.874 --> 42:57.909
- Alright.
- Okay, okay.

43:03.414 --> 43:04.983
Do you like giving things away?

43:06.084 --> 43:08.086
- Do I like giving things away?

43:08.086 --> 43:11.289
Like philanthropy, like charity?

43:11.289 --> 43:13.324
Yeah, like generous like, yes.

43:13.324 --> 43:15.460
I like giving things away, sure.

43:16.361 --> 43:19.698
- And just exactly have you been

43:19.698 --> 43:21.166
working at The
Griddle House for?

43:21.166 --> 43:24.803
- Three weeks.
- Three weeks?

43:24.803 --> 43:29.641
- Well 21 and a half
days to be exact, yeah.

43:29.641 --> 43:32.110
I'm still getting
my sea legs here.

43:32.110 --> 43:32.944
- Oh.

43:35.313 --> 43:36.581
- Is there something wrong?

43:37.949 --> 43:42.520
- Yeah, no, that
was very helpful.

43:43.521 --> 43:44.956
Thank you.

43:44.956 --> 43:49.627
- Okay, can I get you
anything else before you go?

43:51.496 --> 43:54.499
- No I'm fine.
- Okay.

43:54.499 --> 43:55.667
Just let me know.

43:55.667 --> 43:58.069
Oh and thanks for the interview.

44:07.378 --> 44:10.248
- I told you it was
Tiny, not Francis.

44:10.248 --> 44:12.150
Why don't you just
skip to the end?

44:15.987 --> 44:17.689
- Your car is not fixed yet.

44:30.235 --> 44:33.104
- Help, help, I'm being
held against my will.

44:33.104 --> 44:35.473
Look at this, look at the cuffs.

44:40.611 --> 44:43.715
- I know the feeling,
I used to be married.

44:43.715 --> 44:45.050
- So that's him?

44:45.917 --> 44:46.852
- Trust me.

44:52.791 --> 44:55.961
- Is he gonna do anything?
- Just wait.

45:05.837 --> 45:10.275
- Amos, Amos, you gotta go help
me out and take their order.

45:10.275 --> 45:11.642
- Hold up, isn't that your job?

45:11.642 --> 45:13.578
Cook, waitress, cook, waitress.

45:13.578 --> 45:15.046
- I know, but I just can't,

45:15.046 --> 45:16.681
that's the guy I was
telling you about.

45:16.681 --> 45:19.217
- Who, the writer guy?

45:19.217 --> 45:23.588
- Yes, yes that's Professor
Duvet's writing assistant.

45:23.588 --> 45:26.091
- You certainly can't
give him your writing

45:26.091 --> 45:27.725
if you can't even
take his order.

45:27.725 --> 45:30.929
- I know Gus, that's why
I'm asking for help, please.

45:32.197 --> 45:33.965
Amos don't make me, please.

45:33.965 --> 45:36.267
- No one's making you do
anything, give me that.

45:36.267 --> 45:38.603
- Hold up, we got this.
- No you don't have that.

45:38.603 --> 45:39.704
Fix the machine.
- No what are the specials?

45:39.704 --> 45:41.306
We'll just--

45:41.306 --> 45:44.109
- Tell him today he better pop
his peepers back in his head

45:44.109 --> 45:45.410
or I'll pop them for him.

45:45.410 --> 45:47.112
- I'm not gonna
tell him that Gus.

45:52.984 --> 45:56.054
Hi, I'm Amos, can I
get you something?

45:57.555 --> 45:59.390
- Just coffee.
- Me too.

45:59.390 --> 46:01.059
- Two, be right back.

46:01.059 --> 46:02.293
- Sir.
- Yes?

46:04.062 --> 46:05.763
- How is he today?

46:05.763 --> 46:06.597
Gus right?

46:08.533 --> 46:09.567
- You know Gus?

46:10.902 --> 46:12.403
- Well--

46:12.403 --> 46:15.040
- Joe's made him somewhat
famous in our writing class.

46:15.040 --> 46:17.375
- Oh, oh yeah the writing class.

46:19.210 --> 46:20.678
You're writing about Gus.

46:21.913 --> 46:23.148
- The guy's a solid study,

46:23.148 --> 46:25.383
I couldn't make
him up if I tried.

46:25.383 --> 46:27.285
And I had to prove it.

46:27.285 --> 46:28.486
- Really?

46:28.486 --> 46:30.655
Well now you watch
him at your own risk,

46:30.655 --> 46:34.425
but, but hey you know, Francis

46:34.425 --> 46:37.695
she is on the waiting list
for that very class you're in.

46:37.695 --> 46:40.298
- Well it is a great class.
- That's what I hear.

46:41.499 --> 46:43.234
I'll be right back
with your coffees.

46:45.403 --> 46:47.238
They're fans alright.
- What?

46:49.574 --> 46:51.809
This ain't a zoo
and I ain't a llama.

46:52.810 --> 46:54.946
- Told you.
- Classic.

46:54.946 --> 46:56.114
- What're you writing?

46:58.249 --> 47:00.385
- Just your tales of wisdom.

47:01.719 --> 47:02.854
- You making fun of me?

47:03.754 --> 47:05.356
- Oh no, no no no.

47:05.356 --> 47:06.757
- No?

47:06.757 --> 47:09.194
I'm serious, I ain't
for writing about.

47:10.528 --> 47:11.362
Well,

47:13.098 --> 47:14.933
I just won't do
anything interesting.

47:16.067 --> 47:19.770
- That seems like a
big stretch.

47:22.073 --> 47:24.042
- Francis.
- Yeah?

47:24.042 --> 47:25.010
- Come here.
- What did he say?

47:25.010 --> 47:26.411
What did he say?

47:26.411 --> 47:28.013
- Never mind what he said, look,

47:29.280 --> 47:31.482
you've gotta give
this guy your story

47:31.482 --> 47:33.318
because he's an
assistant professor,

47:33.318 --> 47:35.186
he's gotta have some kind
of pull, he could help you.

47:35.186 --> 47:37.222
- I don't know, I
just, I can't Amos.

47:37.222 --> 47:38.689
- You gotta take
this opportunity,

47:38.689 --> 47:39.690
it's knocking on the door.

47:39.690 --> 47:40.926
You gotta open the door

47:40.926 --> 47:42.260
'cause in a minute Gus
is gonna scare them away

47:42.260 --> 47:43.494
and they'll be gone forever.

47:43.494 --> 47:45.130
Now turn around and go, go.
- No Amos.

47:45.130 --> 47:46.697
- I'll go with you.
- Oh Amos.

47:53.004 --> 47:53.905
- This is Francis.

47:55.406 --> 47:58.043
- Coffees and place mats.

48:00.445 --> 48:01.246
Cream?

48:02.113 --> 48:04.049
- We're good.
- Okay.

48:08.319 --> 48:09.687
Sir.
- Yeah?

48:12.457 --> 48:13.291
- Hi.

48:14.292 --> 48:17.362
I'd like to--
- I'm Joe.

48:17.362 --> 48:19.730
- Hi I'm Francis.

48:22.033 --> 48:23.768
- What's up Francis?

48:23.768 --> 48:26.271
- I wanted to talk to you.

48:26.271 --> 48:29.274
The thing is I was wondering
if you just might be,

48:29.274 --> 48:31.542
if you might be willing,

48:31.542 --> 48:34.045
you see I'm on the waiting
list for that class

48:34.045 --> 48:35.680
and I thought maybe
you'd be willing

48:35.680 --> 48:38.683
to take a look at this
story I've been working on.

48:38.683 --> 48:40.385
I mean if you're too busy
or whatever that's fine,

48:40.385 --> 48:44.155
but if you can and
you think it's good

48:44.155 --> 48:46.791
maybe you could talk to
Mr. Duvet about me being--

48:46.791 --> 48:48.526
- Francis, let me
just stop you there

48:48.526 --> 48:51.129
'cause Joe, he
really can't do that,

48:51.129 --> 48:54.099
even if he wanted to, so sorry.

48:55.566 --> 48:56.968
- That's fine.

48:56.968 --> 49:00.205
- It's just that you
know I'm just a student.

49:00.205 --> 49:01.706
- No, no, it's not a problem,

49:01.706 --> 49:04.709
I just thought that maybe you
know you could, but really--

49:04.709 --> 49:05.810
- It's not that,
it's just that--

49:05.810 --> 49:08.746
- No it's fine, I understand.

49:08.746 --> 49:10.681
Now I've got this thing so.

49:12.217 --> 49:14.052
- Well sorry.

49:15.486 --> 49:19.857
- Well you be sure to let me
know if you need anything else.

49:27.732 --> 49:29.000
- Tiny.

49:29.000 --> 49:31.869
♪ I think that's it,
I've had enough ♪

49:31.869 --> 49:34.972
♪ I'm tired of you and
that beat up truck ♪

49:34.972 --> 49:35.806
- Well?

49:35.806 --> 49:37.042
♪ And I'm shipping out

49:37.042 --> 49:39.244
- You're missing
voltage regulator.

49:39.244 --> 49:41.679
Can't do anything without it.

49:42.913 --> 49:43.914
- It's missing?

49:46.684 --> 49:48.119
Well I got here without it.

49:49.587 --> 49:52.190
- Well you ain't
getting it, nevermind.

49:54.792 --> 49:57.895
- I just, I need to
just figure this out.

49:57.895 --> 50:02.900
♪ No you probably won't
depart or get a job ♪

50:03.801 --> 50:06.271
♪ A simple nine to five

50:08.639 --> 50:10.475
- You
doing okay there son?

50:12.910 --> 50:13.911
- Excuse me?

50:17.948 --> 50:20.251
- You like to mix up your corn

50:20.251 --> 50:22.320
into your mashed
potatoes don't you?

50:23.654 --> 50:25.423
- I'm on it baby, I'm on it.

50:25.423 --> 50:28.393
- Along side a turkey club.

50:28.393 --> 50:30.728
- That's easy, give
me something hard.

50:30.728 --> 50:33.631
- With a side of soy sauce.

50:33.631 --> 50:35.133
- I'll see what I got.

50:35.133 --> 50:36.967
- That's my favorite.

50:36.967 --> 50:39.170
- I figured.
- How'd you do that?

50:39.170 --> 50:41.606
- Oh I don't know, it's
just a little knack I got.

50:41.606 --> 50:43.841
Came in real handy
when my kid was little.

50:47.612 --> 50:50.148
I suspect we have
some chatting to do.

50:51.716 --> 50:52.517
Scooch on over would you?
- Okay.

50:55.520 --> 51:00.458
- Now, your mama, she ever
make you set the table?

51:03.128 --> 51:03.961
- Yes.

51:05.830 --> 51:07.932
Most every night.

51:07.932 --> 51:11.269
She's picky like that.
- Picky like what?

51:12.170 --> 51:13.003
- Oh well,

51:15.473 --> 51:18.976
she says if you're
not sick or deceased

51:18.976 --> 51:21.779
you better be
sitting at that table

51:21.779 --> 51:24.349
even if it's take out
on New Year's Eve.

51:24.349 --> 51:26.050
And then she asks us questions.

51:27.485 --> 51:29.387
- Sounds like your mama
knows what a table's for.

51:29.387 --> 51:31.289
What kind of questions?

51:32.723 --> 51:36.927
- You know, normal questions
like how was your day?

51:36.927 --> 51:39.430
What was good, what was bad,

51:39.430 --> 51:43.234
but she calls those
roses and thorns,

51:43.234 --> 51:44.335
it's like the good is the roses

51:44.335 --> 51:46.471
and the bad is the thorns.

51:46.471 --> 51:48.639
And then she makes
you ask your own.

51:50.341 --> 51:51.142
- Okay.

51:52.377 --> 51:53.178
Shoot.

51:54.845 --> 51:56.080
- What?

51:56.080 --> 51:59.184
- Well seems to
me, pretty obvious,

51:59.184 --> 52:02.086
that you came here
looking for some.

52:04.855 --> 52:07.024
- It's that obvious isn't it?

52:07.024 --> 52:09.860
- Why don't you start
with the thorn first,

52:09.860 --> 52:14.165
the real prickly one, the one
poking a hole in your soul.

52:14.165 --> 52:14.999
- Okay.

52:16.534 --> 52:20.971
1977, April 20th did you
give birth to a child,

52:22.340 --> 52:26.043
specifically a boy and
then did you give him away?

52:29.547 --> 52:32.317
- Feels good to ask
something true don't it

52:32.317 --> 52:34.219
even if it is thorny.

52:34.219 --> 52:35.253
- Yes it does.

52:38.389 --> 52:42.293
- No son I did not
have a baby in 1977.

52:43.661 --> 52:47.031
I gave birth to my
son eight years ago.

52:47.031 --> 52:50.067
- You named him Jackson?
- I did.

52:50.067 --> 52:51.969
That's my maiden name.

52:51.969 --> 52:53.304
I didn't have a brother so.

52:55.573 --> 52:56.374
- I see.

52:58.509 --> 52:59.344
- I'm sorry.

53:02.146 --> 53:03.448
- What about her?

53:05.015 --> 53:06.884
You know anything about her?

53:06.884 --> 53:07.885
- Hey order up.

53:09.086 --> 53:11.889
Look, soy sauce, am
I good or am I good?

53:14.792 --> 53:16.727
- Wait, when did she
start coming here?

53:17.895 --> 53:19.530
- Let me get your
order okay son?

53:19.530 --> 53:20.365
- Ma'am.

53:25.002 --> 53:27.405
Ma'am, ma'am please.

53:27.405 --> 53:29.940
Please, when did she
start coming here?

53:29.940 --> 53:31.175
- It just wouldn't be right

53:31.175 --> 53:33.711
to tell somebody else's
story you understand?

53:33.711 --> 53:35.380
- So she's got
something to hide.

53:36.547 --> 53:38.115
- Maybe it's no one's business.

53:39.784 --> 53:42.019
- I think it's my business.

53:44.255 --> 53:49.260
♪ Oh darling won't you
wait for me baby? ♪

53:50.995 --> 53:54.599
♪ I can't go on without you

53:54.599 --> 53:58.235
♪ Oh sure I'll go crazy

53:58.235 --> 54:02.640
♪ Oh darling can we
make this forever ♪

54:04.842 --> 54:05.676
- Hey!

54:09.647 --> 54:10.481
- Oh man.

54:24.362 --> 54:26.431
I could do this all day.

54:28.699 --> 54:31.836
- Dude what's your problem?

54:31.836 --> 54:33.504
- Don't you see the handcuffs?

54:33.504 --> 54:36.841
I'm a criminal man.

54:38.809 --> 54:41.746
- Leave him alone.
- Or what?

54:41.746 --> 54:43.013
He's clearly an idiot

54:44.114 --> 54:47.117
'cause I keep
throwing trash down

54:47.117 --> 54:48.786
and he keeps cleaning it up.

54:50.220 --> 54:53.023
What kind of an idiot keeps
cleaning up the same mess?

54:53.023 --> 54:55.826
- What kind of an idiot
keeps making the same mess?

54:55.826 --> 54:57.495
- It's okay, it's okay.

54:57.495 --> 54:59.630
Listen, I'm just doing my job.

55:00.898 --> 55:04.268
- My point is your
job is stupid.

55:06.003 --> 55:07.372
Really stupid.

55:07.372 --> 55:08.873
- I see you've
finished your pie.

55:08.873 --> 55:11.208
Do you want something
else, are you still hungry?

55:12.510 --> 55:13.344
- What?

55:16.313 --> 55:17.147
- I got it.

55:19.216 --> 55:22.086
In fact anything you
want, it's on the house.

55:24.889 --> 55:29.594
♪ Oh darling won't
you wait for me? ♪

55:29.594 --> 55:31.161
- This is too easy.

55:32.730 --> 55:33.831
- I know he's not famous.

55:34.732 --> 55:35.566
- What?

55:36.701 --> 55:39.169
Oh well yeah you
know, service first.

55:39.169 --> 55:42.039
♪ Oh darling

55:42.039 --> 55:43.641
- What?

55:43.641 --> 55:45.876
- I didn't say anything.

55:45.876 --> 55:47.144
- You still moping?

55:50.014 --> 55:51.248
- Sorry.

55:51.248 --> 55:52.650
- Ain't nothing
to be sorry about.

55:52.650 --> 55:55.920
Sometimes you need a good mope.

55:55.920 --> 55:58.322
This about your book?

55:58.322 --> 56:00.858
- I mean it's a
short story really.

56:02.593 --> 56:03.661
- Whatever.

56:03.661 --> 56:04.929
It's important to you?

56:06.030 --> 56:07.131
- Yeah it is.

56:09.333 --> 56:10.167
Yeah.

56:11.235 --> 56:13.303
- They're not gonna help?

56:14.472 --> 56:15.305
- No.

56:16.674 --> 56:17.508
It's fine.

56:19.710 --> 56:20.745
- It's malarkey.

56:21.946 --> 56:23.147
- What are you gonna do?

56:24.549 --> 56:26.817
- They can't come in here
and write me for free.

56:26.817 --> 56:28.553
- Oh Gus.

56:28.553 --> 56:29.687
- You want to write me?

56:30.588 --> 56:32.089
- Yeah, yeah.
- Fine.

56:32.089 --> 56:33.624
It's gonna cost you.

56:33.624 --> 56:35.560
- Seriously,
seriously Gus.

56:35.560 --> 56:39.163
- You've gotta read
her book or whatever.

56:39.163 --> 56:42.099
- Well I mean actually it's
just a short story so it's--

56:42.099 --> 56:43.901
- I said or whatever.

56:43.901 --> 56:46.571
- I can't promise it's
gonna get her into class.

56:46.571 --> 56:48.305
- What did I say?

56:48.305 --> 56:50.174
- You said read the story.
- Just read it.

56:50.174 --> 56:54.745
- Just read it and I'll quit
with the silent treatment.

56:57.448 --> 56:58.282
- Okay, sure.

57:01.051 --> 57:03.053
- Well you got it?
- What?

57:03.053 --> 57:05.790
- The story.
- Oh yeah.

57:05.790 --> 57:08.192
Oh yeah, I got it, I got
it right here, hold on.

57:09.359 --> 57:11.862
Yeah I do have it right here.

57:11.862 --> 57:12.697
Sorry.

57:14.765 --> 57:16.400
It's right here.

57:16.400 --> 57:17.935
I like to keep it
on yellow paper

57:17.935 --> 57:20.370
so that I can always find it.

57:21.739 --> 57:24.575
- Just give it.
- Alright, alright.

57:28.546 --> 57:30.247
Thank you so much.

57:30.247 --> 57:35.252
It's semi-autobiographical
so I hope that you know.

57:37.988 --> 57:42.627
I mean they say to write
what you know so okay.

57:43.761 --> 57:45.563
I'm just gonna
leave it with you.

57:46.531 --> 57:47.732
I'm just gonna leave it.

57:48.766 --> 57:50.601
Do you want some coffee?

57:50.601 --> 57:52.302
I'll fill up those
coffees, okay.

57:52.302 --> 57:55.272
I'll be right back
with that and whatever.

57:56.674 --> 57:59.443
Oh my god, oh my god, thank
you so much, thank you.

57:59.443 --> 58:02.547
- I hope it's good.
- Oh my god me too.

58:03.413 --> 58:04.682
- Scoot, scoot.

58:05.550 --> 58:06.383
Thank you.

58:07.952 --> 58:08.753
Get a pen.

58:11.088 --> 58:14.158
First, this is as
friendly as I get.

58:15.526 --> 58:18.996
Second, one of you is gonna
buy me a bowl of soup.

58:30.107 --> 58:30.941
- Excuse me.

58:34.344 --> 58:35.179
Excuse me.

58:37.014 --> 58:39.283
- Can I help you?
- I hope so.

58:40.517 --> 58:41.586
- Can you speak up?

58:43.087 --> 58:48.092
- Okay, I was
wondering if I could...

58:50.961 --> 58:52.797
I just--
- Hey.

58:52.797 --> 58:54.031
Careful son, you don't just

58:54.031 --> 58:56.266
go around touching
people's stuff.

58:56.266 --> 58:58.569
- No I wasn't, I'm
sorry I was just,

58:58.569 --> 59:01.338
I want to ask you
a couple questions.

59:03.440 --> 59:05.442
- I don't turn off
the songs for nobody.

59:11.081 --> 59:12.049
- I'm not a nobody.

59:15.352 --> 59:16.186
I'm your son.

59:19.089 --> 59:21.525
You know it and I know it.

59:21.525 --> 59:23.661
- What?
- I can tell.

59:24.729 --> 59:26.430
The way they all treat you.

59:26.430 --> 59:27.765
You've come here for years.

59:29.033 --> 59:31.368
You're the only one
that makes sense.

59:31.368 --> 59:32.970
I've been through everyone else.

59:35.405 --> 59:37.007
I'm Jack.

59:38.208 --> 59:39.844
Jack!

59:39.844 --> 59:41.145
I'm Jack!

59:42.112 --> 59:45.983
Oh, what a shocker, huh?

59:45.983 --> 59:48.919
That I found you
after all these years.

59:48.919 --> 59:53.057
Well maybe if you hadn't
of just tossed me away.

59:53.057 --> 59:57.594
If you could've taken a second
out of your embarrassing life

59:57.594 --> 01:00:00.030
to just find a way to love me

01:00:01.198 --> 01:00:02.599
maybe you wouldn't
be like you are

01:00:03.934 --> 01:00:08.038
and maybe, maybe I
wouldn't be standing here

01:00:08.038 --> 01:00:09.674
yelling at my real mother

01:00:09.674 --> 01:00:13.277
in the middle of The Griddle
House on New Year's Eve.

01:00:13.277 --> 01:00:14.544
- Jack.
- No!

01:00:14.544 --> 01:00:16.947
- Jack, calm down.

01:00:16.947 --> 01:00:19.817
This isn't the time
or the place okay?

01:00:19.817 --> 01:00:20.951
Calm down.

01:00:20.951 --> 01:00:23.420
- Tiny, he don't mean it.

01:00:23.420 --> 01:00:24.955
- Oh no.

01:00:24.955 --> 01:00:26.190
Right there's where
you're sideways Gus

01:00:26.190 --> 01:00:29.794
because you know
what he means it.

01:00:31.361 --> 01:00:32.930
Just look at him,
look at his face

01:00:32.930 --> 01:00:36.667
and you can see how
terrible much he means it.

01:00:36.667 --> 01:00:39.169
Right down to the bone
he means it, every word.

01:00:41.071 --> 01:00:43.007
And the crazy thing
is that he's right.

01:00:46.010 --> 01:00:48.879
About how I lived,
what I've done.

01:00:51.215 --> 01:00:52.750
He's right about all of it

01:00:52.750 --> 01:00:57.722
except for one little
thing, I'm not his mama.

01:00:59.456 --> 01:01:00.958
I've never had a baby of my own.

01:01:03.393 --> 01:01:05.329
- Tiny wait I wanted
to give you something

01:01:05.329 --> 01:01:07.131
for your birthday at midnight,

01:01:07.131 --> 01:01:08.298
but I can give it to you now.

01:01:08.298 --> 01:01:10.968
- Can't stop.
- Tiny your car's broke.

01:01:21.045 --> 01:01:21.879
- Come on.

01:01:27.985 --> 01:01:30.120
- So it was none of them?

01:01:30.120 --> 01:01:31.989
Great job on your
terrible story.

01:01:31.989 --> 01:01:33.090
- Oh it gets better.

01:02:25.409 --> 01:02:30.414
Oh I didn't know you were
waiting, but you can--

01:02:31.581 --> 01:02:32.850
- I wasn't, not
for the bathroom.

01:02:36.120 --> 01:02:37.354
That was awkward.

01:02:39.023 --> 01:02:39.857
- What?

01:02:41.258 --> 01:02:45.729
- Think of the most awful thing
that happened tonight, that.

01:02:48.198 --> 01:02:50.167
- Yeah, I know.

01:02:50.167 --> 01:02:52.069
- Things must be
pretty rough at home?

01:02:53.470 --> 01:02:55.239
- They're not great.

01:02:55.239 --> 01:02:56.440
- Terrible parents?

01:02:58.075 --> 01:02:59.043
- Not great.

01:02:59.043 --> 01:03:01.979
- Don't love you, resent you,

01:03:01.979 --> 01:03:04.548
wish you were out
of their lives?

01:03:04.548 --> 01:03:05.549
Something like that?

01:03:06.884 --> 01:03:07.717
- No, no.

01:03:09.686 --> 01:03:13.390
You know, we don't
connect lately so.

01:03:14.992 --> 01:03:16.927
- You don't connect.

01:03:16.927 --> 01:03:18.128
You thought you would connect

01:03:18.128 --> 01:03:20.597
with a total stranger
in a coffee shop?

01:03:20.597 --> 01:03:21.832
- What?

01:03:21.832 --> 01:03:24.301
What are you trying
to understand me?

01:03:24.301 --> 01:03:25.735
Trying to like figure me out?

01:03:30.407 --> 01:03:33.110
- People don't get to
pick their family son.

01:03:35.112 --> 01:03:36.513
Except sometimes they do.

01:03:37.681 --> 01:03:41.618
I just, I feel like that
should mean something.

01:03:44.521 --> 01:03:45.355
- Thank you.

01:04:02.907 --> 01:04:03.740
- Oh hey hon.

01:04:07.077 --> 01:04:11.215
Listen Tiny's a big girl,
she makes her own decisions.

01:04:12.316 --> 01:04:14.518
It ain't all on you, okay?

01:04:18.989 --> 01:04:22.492
- Listen, just don't
read that story okay--

01:04:22.492 --> 01:04:23.660
- We already did.

01:04:24.594 --> 01:04:25.562
- Oh.
- It's great.

01:04:25.562 --> 01:04:28.132
- Yeah it's really beautiful.

01:04:28.132 --> 01:04:31.068
- Well I'm sure it needs a
lot of work so please just--

01:04:31.068 --> 01:04:32.736
- Not that I saw.

01:04:32.736 --> 01:04:36.240
Look I'll definitely
talk to Duvet for you,

01:04:36.240 --> 01:04:39.643
but we're actually interested
in your story ourselves.

01:04:39.643 --> 01:04:41.912
You see we just launched
a writing magazine

01:04:41.912 --> 01:04:44.681
where basically new writers
can submit their stuff

01:04:44.681 --> 01:04:47.217
and we're convinced that
there's a whole book here.

01:04:47.217 --> 01:04:50.120
- I just, I don't really
know what to say so.

01:04:50.120 --> 01:04:52.589
- Yes will do.
- How about maybe?

01:04:52.589 --> 01:04:53.823
- What?

01:04:53.823 --> 01:04:55.092
- It's just not
my story to tell.

01:04:56.026 --> 01:04:57.861
I've gotta run it by someone.

01:04:57.861 --> 01:04:59.829
- Well any idea when you'll
have an answer for us?

01:04:59.829 --> 01:05:02.699
- That's fine, listen,
I'll leave my contact info

01:05:02.699 --> 01:05:05.069
and just whenever,
if ever feels right,

01:05:05.069 --> 01:05:06.303
just give me a call--

01:05:06.303 --> 01:05:08.338
- You know what I'm
sorry I've got to go.

01:05:08.338 --> 01:05:12.276
- I think this should
probably cover it.

01:05:12.276 --> 01:05:14.544
- Goodness, you didn't
get the filet mignon.

01:05:15.745 --> 01:05:17.514
Take it, save it for yourself.

01:05:19.416 --> 01:05:20.417
- Thank you.

01:05:36.166 --> 01:05:37.167
Hey.

01:05:37.167 --> 01:05:38.002
- Hey.

01:05:38.002 --> 01:05:39.736
- You like my car?

01:05:39.736 --> 01:05:41.405
- Are you
going somewhere?

01:05:42.539 --> 01:05:45.475
- Yeah, after all that
I think it's just,

01:05:45.475 --> 01:05:46.876
you know, best if I head on.

01:05:48.012 --> 01:05:50.347
- You know sometimes
in life we just,

01:05:50.347 --> 01:05:52.349
we don't have any
choice but to move on.

01:05:54.184 --> 01:05:55.419
- Right.

01:05:55.419 --> 01:05:58.422
- Hey, did you find what
you were looking for?

01:06:01.558 --> 01:06:02.359
- No.

01:06:03.760 --> 01:06:06.596
But I sure made a fool
of myself trying to.

01:06:06.596 --> 01:06:08.565
- No, no you didn't, no.

01:06:10.067 --> 01:06:14.471
I mean Phil, sometimes
the only choice we have

01:06:14.471 --> 01:06:18.408
is to just give up
the search you know?

01:06:19.409 --> 01:06:20.244
- Yeah.

01:06:21.678 --> 01:06:25.282
By the way my name isn't
actually Phil, it's Jack.

01:06:27.651 --> 01:06:30.754
I mean I yelled it
pretty loud in there so.

01:06:30.754 --> 01:06:31.721
- Yeah I know.

01:06:33.290 --> 01:06:34.124
I know.

01:06:40.497 --> 01:06:42.599
You know what nevermind.

01:06:42.599 --> 01:06:45.035
Just, Happy New Year.

01:06:47.137 --> 01:06:49.706
And I want you to
drive safe okay.

01:06:49.706 --> 01:06:53.343
- Yeah, thanks, Happy New Year.

01:09:04.707 --> 01:09:05.609
- Hey.
- Hi.

01:09:06.776 --> 01:09:08.978
- I'm gonna go, so.

01:09:08.978 --> 01:09:10.747
- Okay.
- Okay.

01:10:23.353 --> 01:10:25.522
- Amos get me all
the marshmallows you got.

01:10:25.522 --> 01:10:27.624
- Looks like somebody's
done beat you to it.

01:10:33.663 --> 01:10:34.764
- Jack what?

01:10:35.632 --> 01:10:36.633
- Where's Francis?

01:10:38.201 --> 01:10:39.769
- Well her shift was over honey.

01:10:41.938 --> 01:10:42.939
- Are you serious?

01:10:46.075 --> 01:10:46.876
She's gone.

01:10:49.145 --> 01:10:52.682
So what, she wrote
that whole story,

01:10:52.682 --> 01:10:57.654
snuck it into my car
like that, she's gone?

01:10:58.855 --> 01:11:00.089
She didn't even want
to say goodbye to me.

01:11:00.089 --> 01:11:01.257
- Come have a seat
with me, okay?

01:11:08.064 --> 01:11:13.069
Hey, her sharing that story
with you, that was big for her.

01:11:15.872 --> 01:11:20.877
- All I ever wanted I thought
was to meet my birth mom.

01:11:24.748 --> 01:11:27.351
Stupid, just so stupid.

01:11:27.351 --> 01:11:29.586
- If you allow me to say so

01:11:30.787 --> 01:11:32.989
I believe you did get
to meet your birth mom

01:11:32.989 --> 01:11:34.891
at least just a little bit.

01:11:34.891 --> 01:11:39.896
The time you spent here, the
story that she shared with you,

01:11:40.630 --> 01:11:43.600
that is her truest self

01:11:45.068 --> 01:11:48.104
and she did say
goodbye in her own way.

01:11:51.841 --> 01:11:54.744
She said that she'd never
have the perfect words

01:11:54.744 --> 01:11:57.080
so she wrote them instead.

01:12:07.256 --> 01:12:12.261
- For the boy who is already
the oak inside the acorn.

01:12:16.400 --> 01:12:18.067
What does that mean?

01:12:18.067 --> 01:12:19.903
- I think what
she's trying to say

01:12:20.770 --> 01:12:23.707
is that she already sees in you

01:12:23.707 --> 01:12:25.274
everything you're going to be.

01:12:26.443 --> 01:12:29.245
That she wanted you to
be, you already are.

01:12:31.214 --> 01:12:32.048
You see?

01:12:37.153 --> 01:12:38.187
- Just one thing.

01:12:39.456 --> 01:12:44.461
When I first read this letter

01:12:46.095 --> 01:12:48.965
she said that she'd been
coming to The Griddle House

01:12:48.965 --> 01:12:51.435
for years but when I asked her

01:12:51.435 --> 01:12:54.370
she said she only worked
here for three weeks.

01:12:56.372 --> 01:12:59.709
- Both, she's been
here for years

01:12:59.709 --> 01:13:01.945
and has only been working
here for a few weeks.

01:13:05.449 --> 01:13:07.851
I got something for
you, one second.

01:13:12.255 --> 01:13:16.092
When I got the blues
I play the crosswords.

01:13:17.193 --> 01:13:18.695
And I'm gonna share
that with you.

01:13:21.164 --> 01:13:22.699
Can you help me with four down?

01:13:26.670 --> 01:13:28.137
- Could be punk.

01:13:31.641 --> 01:13:33.209
- Excuse me.

01:13:33.209 --> 01:13:34.310
- Sorry, sorry.

01:13:34.310 --> 01:13:37.180
Give me the poundy, smashy now.

01:13:38.114 --> 01:13:39.649
Thank you.

01:13:39.649 --> 01:13:43.453
Alright give me the one that
goes--

01:13:43.453 --> 01:13:44.287
Thank you.

01:13:46.189 --> 01:13:47.423
I think that...

01:13:52.228 --> 01:13:53.530
She's fixed.

01:13:53.530 --> 01:13:54.330
- Really?

01:13:54.330 --> 01:13:55.565
- Yep, great.

01:13:55.565 --> 01:13:56.766
Now here we land
on the signature,

01:13:56.766 --> 01:13:58.034
can we get the
owner's signature?

01:13:58.034 --> 01:14:00.003
- Oh, oh, yeah,
yeah.

01:14:00.003 --> 01:14:00.870
Mr. Peterson.

01:14:02.005 --> 01:14:03.773
The twin towers
need your signature.

01:14:03.773 --> 01:14:04.608
- Sure thing.

01:14:05.875 --> 01:14:07.477
- No way.

01:14:09.913 --> 01:14:11.147
- Alright.
- Thank you gentlemen.

01:14:11.147 --> 01:14:13.850
- Oh our pleasure, she
is a lovely machine.

01:14:13.850 --> 01:14:15.084
- Thank you very much.

01:14:15.084 --> 01:14:16.285
- I was wondering if we
could get some menus.

01:14:16.285 --> 01:14:17.386
I think we're gonna
stay for dinner.

01:14:17.386 --> 01:14:19.055
- Absolutely.
- Great.

01:14:19.055 --> 01:14:21.357
- On the house.
- Why thank you.

01:14:23.326 --> 01:14:26.062
- Dude, come on.

01:14:27.196 --> 01:14:28.965
You're the owner?

01:14:28.965 --> 01:14:31.167
- No one really owns anything,

01:14:31.167 --> 01:14:33.169
but this place was
entrusted to me.

01:14:33.169 --> 01:14:35.705
- Whatever, you
paid their checks

01:14:35.705 --> 01:14:37.874
and you're the one
cleaning up the messes?

01:14:37.874 --> 01:14:39.075
- Yeah.

01:14:39.075 --> 01:14:40.476
I really don't mind.

01:14:40.476 --> 01:14:43.446
- Dude if I were you I wouldn't
even be here right now.

01:14:43.446 --> 01:14:46.750
I'd be at home, kicking back,

01:14:46.750 --> 01:14:50.520
watching a big screen
TV and counting my cash.

01:14:50.520 --> 01:14:52.488
- I don't do this for the money.

01:14:52.488 --> 01:14:53.723
- What?

01:14:53.723 --> 01:14:56.526
- You can't trust
money or things.

01:14:57.927 --> 01:15:01.631
- Well, that's about
all I do trust.

01:15:03.099 --> 01:15:05.702
- And that's why you're the
only one here in handcuffs.

01:15:07.103 --> 01:15:11.074
You really want to be free
follow what's in here.

01:15:24.788 --> 01:15:25.855
- Well what do you know

01:15:25.855 --> 01:15:28.992
it's Officer Darcy just in time.

01:15:28.992 --> 01:15:29.959
- Oh yeah?
- Yeah.

01:15:30.827 --> 01:15:32.596
- Mason is it true?

01:15:32.596 --> 01:15:35.398
Did you steal a Sega
Genetics from the Target?

01:15:35.398 --> 01:15:36.600
- Genesis.

01:15:36.600 --> 01:15:38.735
- A Sega Genesis
from the Target?

01:15:38.735 --> 01:15:43.439
- Yes ma'am but
it's just Target.

01:15:43.439 --> 01:15:45.041
- Mason why?

01:15:45.041 --> 01:15:46.309
- I don't know.

01:15:46.309 --> 01:15:48.211
- Don't we give you
everything you need?

01:15:52.916 --> 01:15:55.384
Needless to say I am
very disappointed in you.

01:15:55.384 --> 01:15:57.787
Your father is gonna
be beside himself.

01:15:57.787 --> 01:15:58.622
- I know.

01:15:59.756 --> 01:16:01.691
- What am I gonna do with you?

01:16:01.691 --> 01:16:03.627
- Maybe he could
stay here with us.

01:16:03.627 --> 01:16:06.162
- Oh I don't know.

01:16:06.162 --> 01:16:08.064
- You want him to
straighten out?

01:16:08.064 --> 01:16:09.766
I can't imagine a better place.

01:16:11.768 --> 01:16:15.171
- Well thank you,
I'll be in touch.

01:16:15.171 --> 01:16:15.972
Come on Mason.

01:16:29.485 --> 01:16:30.453
Thank you Officer.

01:16:32.088 --> 01:16:34.658
- Would the
hero like a cup of Joe?

01:16:34.658 --> 01:16:36.525
- Yeah, I'll hang out.

01:16:46.903 --> 01:16:47.737
- Hey.

01:16:49.505 --> 01:16:51.107
- There you are Tiny.

01:16:52.575 --> 01:16:57.013
- Please don't, I mean do,
but just give me a minute.

01:16:59.983 --> 01:17:02.351
Now you y'all,
y'all bear with me.

01:17:02.351 --> 01:17:06.489
Someone once told
me that the truth

01:17:06.489 --> 01:17:07.791
will make your voice shake

01:17:09.192 --> 01:17:13.496
and it'll gut you too sometimes
to hear all that point blank

01:17:13.496 --> 01:17:17.333
but that ain't the worse that
can happen to someone like me

01:17:17.333 --> 01:17:20.670
to hear something so hard and
ugly and true about yourself

01:17:20.670 --> 01:17:24.373
that you can't help but you
know run into it head long.

01:17:25.574 --> 01:17:26.710
That ain't the worst.

01:17:28.544 --> 01:17:33.549
The worst is trolling around
every night of your life

01:17:34.718 --> 01:17:36.085
waiting for a pick up
and pretending like

01:17:37.386 --> 01:17:39.088
that's the only truth
that there'll ever be

01:17:39.088 --> 01:17:41.324
for you 'cause you're trouble

01:17:42.959 --> 01:17:45.328
and trouble can't
hope for no more.

01:17:45.328 --> 01:17:47.263
- Tiny.
- No.

01:17:47.263 --> 01:17:51.701
No maybe that's what
I'm trying to say here,

01:17:51.701 --> 01:17:55.805
that my truth, no matter
how hard I say it,

01:17:57.106 --> 01:18:00.744
it isn't true, I don't
believe it anymore.

01:18:00.744 --> 01:18:03.646
- You don't?
- Nope.

01:18:03.646 --> 01:18:04.914
What you've been saying to me

01:18:04.914 --> 01:18:06.883
for as long as I've
been coming in here,

01:18:08.217 --> 01:18:11.620
that my heart is worth fighting
for, worth loving even,

01:18:13.189 --> 01:18:15.925
I'm starting to believe it.

01:18:19.328 --> 01:18:20.663
- Anything else?

01:18:22.431 --> 01:18:24.267
- That I ain't no
trouble for anyone.

01:18:25.969 --> 01:18:28.271
- How's that truth feel
when you say it Tiny?

01:18:29.806 --> 01:18:32.308
- Like my heart's
been waiting 34 years

01:18:32.308 --> 01:18:34.077
for my mouth to say it out loud.

01:18:35.478 --> 01:18:38.247
- Feels good right,
like good home cooking.

01:18:43.052 --> 01:18:45.789
- Handlethorpes, you
got a sledgehammer?

01:18:48.958 --> 01:18:49.793
Oh.

01:18:52.228 --> 01:18:53.229
Get it girl.

01:18:58.401 --> 01:18:59.668
- This calls for a toast.

01:19:02.705 --> 01:19:03.639
I almost forgot.

01:19:05.241 --> 01:19:06.742
Mae-Bee you want
to count us down?

01:19:06.742 --> 01:19:09.612
- Okay, goodness is it that
time already, okay here we go.

01:19:09.612 --> 01:19:13.082
10.
- Nine, eight, seven,

01:19:13.082 --> 01:19:17.787
six, five, four,
three, two, one.

01:19:17.787 --> 01:19:19.655
Happy New Year!

01:19:20.857 --> 01:19:22.625
- And happy birthday Tiny.

01:19:22.625 --> 01:19:23.927
- Happy New Year.

01:19:23.927 --> 01:19:25.328
Happy New Year.

01:19:25.328 --> 01:19:27.196
- Okay well.

